article.headline: Jackson St. 81, UC Davis 57
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Grant Maxey scored 19 points and Jackson State snapped a five-game losing streak with an 81-57 victory over UC Davis on Friday night. Jackson State (2-10) scored the last seven points of the first half and the first 10 of the second half to take a 50-31 lead with 15:43 left. Jeremy Caldwell added 17 points and 10 rebounds and Garrison Johnson scored 14 for Jackson State, which outrebounded UC Davis 31-20 and hit 55 percent of its shots. UC Davis (5-6) faded in the second half, making only 10 of 26 shots. Vince Oliver led UC Davis with 16 points, Kyle Brucculeri had 14 and Shane Hanson scored 10.
